verses.verse: A Song of Ascents. Unto thee do I lift up <WH5375> mine eyes <WH5869>, O thou that sittest <WH3427> in the heavens <WH8064>.

Behold <WH5869>, as the eyes of servants <WH5650> look unto the hand <WH3027> of their master <WH113>, As the eyes <WH5869> of a maid <WH8198> unto the hand <WH3027> of her mistress <WH1404>; So our eyes <WH5869> look unto Jehovah <WH3068> our God <WH430>, Until he have mercy upon us <WH2603>.
Have mercy <WH2603> upon us <WH3068>, O Jehovah, have mercy <WH2603> upon us <WH7227>; For we are exceedingly filled <WH7646> with contempt <WH937>.
Our soul <WH5315> is exceedingly <WH7227> filled <WH7646> With the scoffing <WH3933> of those that are at ease <WH7600>, And with the contempt <WH937> of the proud <WH1343>.
